CHOLERA, IMPORTED - CHINA (HONG KONG) & MAYOTTE: REQUEST FOR INFO
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: 5 Jun 2001 10:23
From: Marianne Hopp <mhopp@iri.columbia.edu>
Source: WHO/WER Notifications of diseases received from 25 to 31 May 2001
[edited]

One imported non-fatal case was reported from the Special Administrative
Region (SAR) of China with date of onset given as the week of 7-14 May
2001. [No details given of origin or type. - Mod.JW]
******
[2]
Date: 8 Jun 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: RTHK Radio 3 audio web site, Hong Kong [in English] 0800 GMT 5 Jun
2001 [edited]

The Department of Health has confirmed that a 61-year-old woman from Kwai
Chung was admitted to the Princess Margaret Hospital over the weekend and
is now in critical condition. A spokesman said she had not travelled
outside Hong Kong during the incubation period and the hospital has
classified the case as a local one. The source of the infection is being
investigated. [No details of type. This is clearly a different case than
the one above. - Mod.JW]
******
[3]
Date: 8 Jun 2001 10:23
From: Marianne Hopp <mhopp@iri.columbia.edu>
Source: WHO/WER Notifications received from 1 to 7 June 2001 [edited]

One imported non-fatal case was reported from Mayotte (French territorial
collectivity) with date of onset(?) given as 16 Jan 2001. [No details given
of origin or type. Mayotte is one of the Comoros Islands, lying between
Mozambique & Madagascar. - Mod.JW]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[As always, ProMED-mail would like to know the origin of the imported cases
and the strain involved -- we are looking for the spread of O139. - Mod.JW]
